@node Top
@top ny - Nytrix Tool

@command{ny} runs source, emits native binaries, opens the REPL, and dispatches
the built-in project tools.

@menu
* Run::          Source execution and native output.
* Subcommands::  Project, package, docs, format, test, and perf tools.
* Options::      Common flags.
* Environment::  Common environment variables.
* Examples::     Short command examples.
* See Also::     Markdown documentation.
@end menu

@node Run
@chapter Run

@table @code
@item ny
Start the REPL, or read piped stdin as REPL batch input.
@item ny file.ny
Compile and run a file through the default JIT path.
@item ny -c @var{CODE}
Run inline source.
@item ny -ic @var{CODE}, ny -ci @var{CODE}
Run inline source, then continue in the REPL.
@item ny --repl < file.ny
Compile stdin source once through the REPL batch path.
@item ny -run file.ny
Build a temporary native executable and run it.
@item ny -o app file.ny
Emit a native executable.
@item ny -i, ny --interactive, ny --plain-repl
Start an explicit REPL. @code{--plain-repl} disables line-editing UI.
@end table

Prompt commands include @code{:snapshot [snapfile] [-o executable]} and
@code{:load snapfile}.

@node Subcommands
@chapter Subcommands

@table @code
@item ny new [dir]
Create a project scaffold with manifest, source entry, README, and gitignore.
@item ny pkg @var{command}
Manage source packages, repositories, lockfiles, roots, and installs.
@item ny fmt [mode] [paths...]
Format Nytrix source and audit for trim, bloat, bugs, modules, profiles,
layouts, contracts, FFI, constants, specialization, and compile-time
generation candidates.
@item ny doc search [--docs|--symbols] query
Search prose pages, modules, exported symbols, docstrings, and keyword tags.
@item ny doc get query
Print the closest reference entry.
@item ny doc -o docs
Generate the static HTML reference.
@item ny test [paths...] [--pattern name]
Run runtime, error, stdlib, or selected test checks.
@item ny perf
Run maintained performance checks and comparison workflows.
@item ny make [target]
Native build wrapper. Common targets: @code{bin}, @code{test}, @code{std},
@code{docs}, @code{perf}, @code{install}.
@end table

@section Package Commands

@table @code
@item ny pkg init [name]
Create @file{ny.pkg.json}.
@item ny pkg add name source
Add, install, and lock a dependency.
@item ny get name
Resolve a registry or repository package and install it.
@item ny pkg install, sync, update, uninstall, list
Maintain installed dependencies and the lockfile.
@item ny pkg repo add/list/sync/path/remove
Manage package repositories.
@item ny pkg search [--interactive] query
Search packages. The interactive picker is built into @command{ny}.
@item ny pkg path, info, venv, registry
Inspect package roots, metadata, venv path, and registries.
@end table

Source forms include local paths, @code{git+} URLs, SSH git sources, archives,
and repository packages. Install roots include @file{./ny_modules},
@file{./vendor/ny_modules}, @file{./.nytrix/venv/lib}, user/global roots,
system roots, and @code{--root path}.

@node Options
@chapter Options

@section Diagnostics And Safety

@table @code
@item --color=auto|always|never
Control diagnostic color.
@item --diag-compact --collect-errors
Collect a dense failure set.
@item --diag-rich
Print wider source context.
@item --safe-mode, --safe, --mode=safe
Use default type checks plus ownership/borrow checks, RC/RAII cleanup, strict
effect/alias policy, and raw-memory diagnostics.
@item --strict, --strict-types, --borrow-check, --ownership-strict
Enable focused static checks.
@item --heap=gc, -gc
Enable the opt-in runtime collector.
@item --max-errors=N
Parser error cap. Use @code{0} to disable the cap.
@end table

@section Optimization And Output

@table @code
@item -O0, -O1, -O2, -O3, -O
Set optimization level. Native output defaults to @code{-O2}; JIT/REPL default
to @code{-O0}. @code{-O} aliases @code{-O2}.
@item --profile=speed|balanced|compile|size|none|peak
Select the optimization profile. @code{peak} favors native benchmark speed over
compile latency.
@item --fast
High optimization convenience mode with stripped output by default.
@item -emit-only
Emit output without executing.
@item -strip, -no-strip
Choose stripped or unstripped native output.
@item -L DIR, -l LIB
Add native linker search paths and libraries.
@end table

@section Debugging

@table @code
@item -v, -vv, -vvv, --debug
Increase logging.
@item -time, -prof, -dump-stats
Print timing, profiling, or compiler statistics.
@item -dump-ast, -dump-tokens, -dump-llvm, -dump-funcs, -dump-symbols
Inspect compiler/runtime artifacts.
@item --emit-ir=PATH, --emit-asm=PATH
Write LLVM IR or assembly.
@item --dump-on-error
Write debug source/IR artifacts on failure.
@item -trace
Enable execution tracing.
@end table

@node Environment
@chapter Environment

Prefer CLI flags in shared scripts. Common environment variables:

@table @code
@item NYTRIX_STD_PATH, NYTRIX_STD_PREBUILT, NYTRIX_BUILD_STD_PATH
Stdlib lookup and generated stdlib source.
@item NYTRIX_HOST_TRIPLE, NYTRIX_ARM_FLOAT_ABI
Host target tuning.
@item NYTRIX_HOST_CFLAGS, NYTRIX_HOST_LDFLAGS
Host compiler and linker flags.
@item NYTRIX_TRACE_COMPTIME_MACRO
Trace native compile-time macro expansion.
@item NYTRIX_EFFECT_ASYNC_LOWERING
Enable eligible async-effect lowering globally.
@end table

Use @code{ny --help env} for the full environment list.

@node Examples
@chapter Examples

@example
ny --version
ny -c 'print(1 + 1)'
ny file.ny
ny -run file.ny
ny -O3 --profile=peak -o app bench.ny
ny fmt --check lib
ny fmt --cloc --top 20 lib
ny doc search --symbols json_decode
ny test --pattern import
ny pkg add helper ./deps/helper
@end example

